communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: FTC: Straxis Technology
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I would like copies of all complaints to the Federal Trade Commission or investigations carried out, regarding the following company:

https://www.straxis.com/about.php

Straxis Technology
1305 E. 15th Street
Tulsa, Oklahoma  74120

Of particular interest is any thing related to complaints made regarding their data collection policies, as is mentioned in this article:

https://taskandpurpose.com/news/504-military-intelligence-app/

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robert Delaware

communications.subject: Thank you
communications.communication:
Hello,

Thank you for submitting your Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) request to the Federal Trade Commission (FTC). Someone from our office will reach out to you as soon as possible regarding the status of your request.

Sincerely,

The FTC FOIA Unit

title: shapefile for election precincts in March 2024 election

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: shapefile for election precincts in March 2024 election
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

a GIS shapefile of the electoral precincts as they defined for the March, 2024 election

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Forest Gregg
